Playing with CSS Variables and JS

--> different than SASS
    --->controlled using javascript

Example:

3 Variables: Spacing, Blur and Base Color

Declaring in CSS:

  html {  (Using any selector)

      --base: #ff0000; (values remain the same as usual)
      --spacing: 10px;
      --blur: 10px;
}

Using the declared CSS Variables:

  img {
    
      padding: var(--spacing);
      background: var(--base);
      filter: blur(var--blur);

}

So to updates the variable's value you change it in your declaration of the variables.

